                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-08-11</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>My copy of this book is yellowed, tattered and over 30 years old.  Nonetheless, I can open to any page and find a bit of timeless wisdom and truth.  I've worked in difficult situations with groups and individuals for the past ten years.  I've worked with, convicts, hardcore addicts and the mentally ill.  I've also worked with highly educated, wealthy, distinguished individuals.  I'm here to tell you that the techniques in this book will work with all people.<p>No one likes to be criticized or condemned.  We all want to save face and feel important.  This book teaches you the power of humility and the art of getting what you want while working cooperatively and harmoniously with others.<p>If you find yourself struggling at your current job or if you're in conflict with your co-workers or employees, I'd recommend trying some of the techniques and principles outlined in this book.</span>
                  
